-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
screen-session  requires a modified version of GNU Screen,
it uses "ps", "pgrep" and reads /proc filesystem.


Tested on:

    Linux, Python 2.5.2 and 2.7.2
    FreeBSD 8.1, Python 2.6.5 (with mounted procfs)
    OpenSolaris, Python 2.4.4


screen-4.1.0 bundled with screen-session:

    - add "tty" command
    - make "group" queryable
    - associate focuminsize with the layout
    - add "dumpscreen window|layout" command


gnu_screen.diff changes:

    - add "tty" command
    - make "group" queryable
    - associate focuminsize with the layout
    - add "dumpscreen window|layout" command


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation - part 1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (screen-session is installed
into the /usr/local/ namespace by default), you can also disable colors
by removing "-DCOLOR".

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install
screen-session:

    make clean
    make

    make install # (if necessary as root)

Note that the installation step is optional, only compilation is necessary.
Just link to from your PATH to
screen-session/ScreenSession/screen-session


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation - part 2 - option 1 - using Screen distribution supplied
                                   with screen-session
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Compile and install Screen:

    cd screen-session/screen-4.1.0

    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
    make

    sudo make install


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation - part 2 - option 2 - patching Screen on your own
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Make sure you have a recent version of Screen and apply the necessary
patch (gnu_screen.diff):

    git clone git://git.sv.gnu.org/screen.git screen
    cd screen

    git apply --whitespace=nowarn ../screen-session/gnu_screen.diff

    cd src
    autoreconf
    autoheader

    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
    make

    sudo make install

Alternatively, download and compile prepatched Screen from:
https://github.com/skoneka/escreen/downloads
